SIMPLE: freckle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freckle
<hw>Freck"le</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧k"k'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim.,
from the same root as <ets>freak</ets>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A small yellowish or brownish spot in the skin,
particularly on the face, neck, or hands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any small spot or discoloration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freckle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Freckle
<hw>Frec"kle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Freckled</conjf> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧k"k'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Freckling</conjf>
<pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧k"kl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To sprinkle or mark with
freckles or small discolored spots; to spot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 594 --></p>

<p><ent>Freckle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Freckle
<hw>Frec"kle</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧k"k'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To
become covered or marked with freckles; to be spotted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freckled</ent>⟦br⟧
